Best way to determine exact secrets

Use this order:

1. Check the app config in code

This tells you what variables/properties the app expects.

2. Check EC2 runtime config

This tells you what real values are currently being supplied.

3. Compare both

This tells you:
	•	which config values are required
	•	which ones are environment-specific
	•	which ones are secrets
	•	which ones can become ConfigMap values instead of secrets

⸻

Secrets vs non-secrets

Put in Kubernetes Secret

Use Secret for:
	•	passwords
	•	tokens
	•	client secrets
	•	private keys
	•	DB credentials

Put in ConfigMap or plain env

Use non-secret config for:
	•	app profile
	•	service URLs
	•	port
	•	log level
	•	feature flags

