Practical answer to your DB question

Yes — DB is the first thing you should verify.

Because if the app connects to a DB and those details are missing or wrong, the pod may start and immediately fail.

You need to know:
	•	DB type
	•	DB endpoint/host
	•	DB name
	•	DB username/password
	•	whether STG DB is the same as current EC2 environment or different
	•	whether network access from EKS to DB is already allowed

That last point matters too:
even if the secret is correct, the DB connection can still fail if:
	•	security groups block it
	•	subnet routing blocks it
	•	DB whitelist blocks it

